so if someone infected coughs/sneezes in the air, and the virus lingers in water droplets floats down to the floor, and an uninfected person walks on that contaminated floor taints their own boots/shoes, then travels abroad, and tracks the disease tainting the footwear contaminates everywhere the person goes, that person even though "not infected at all" but is now a walking "super-spreader", too !!!!????

if that person kicks off the footwear, and these are placed near a ventilated corridor, that disease may be blown off the footwear, into the air (HVAC) system to spread it around to others to breathe it in, and they all get infected from a tainted pair of footwear, used by someone who never got infected (by pure chance).

meanwhile, that person previously with the contaminated footwear is now wearing a totally different pair of boots/shoes that are uncontaminated, and still uninfected, too!!! goes about life completely oblivious to the unusual circumstances that spread a disease from one place, to many other places far far away, infected many many others!!!

so, there's no guarantee any "super-spreader" of a disease is even infected at all, except by chance, infected like others, on an unlikely "roundabout" indirect pathway(s)!!!
